ActivityFeed.summary: API method for retrieving the activity feed for a member's groups

Attendance.summary: Lists attendance records for Meetup events

Categories.summary: Returns a list of Meetup group categories

Checkins.summary: This method returns checkins for an event. To post checkins, see /2/checkin.

Checkinv2.summary: This method posts event checkins that can be retrieved by /2/checkins. Event attendees may check in themselves and others in the group.

ChunkedHTTPOpenVenuesStream.summary:
Live HTTP stream of the creation and modification of public Meetup venues using
chunked encoding
to maintian a persistent connection with a client. The connection will only be
terminiated for server maintenance or a connection error. It is suitable for
low-level HTTP clients rather than web browsers.

Cities.summary: API method for accessing meetup cities

CommentLikes.summary: Api for listing likes of a given event comment

Comments.summary: API method for accessing meetup group comments

Commentsv2.summary: This method returns messages that appear under "Talk about this Meetup". To post messages, see the corresponding write method.

CommunityEdit.summary: For container owners. API method for removing a community. All events of the community will be removed as well.

Concierge.summary: Recommends upcoming meetups for the authorized member.

EventCommentFlag.summary: This method creates a spam report for comment content

EventCommentUnsubscribe.summary: Unsubscribe to notifications for updates to a given comment thread

EventCommentv2.summary: This method posts messages that appear under "Talk about this Meetup".

EventRating.summary: This method allows members to posts rating for an event after it's occurred. Only permitted for members who rsvp'd "yes" or "maybe" to the event

EventSeedEdit.summary: For container owners. API method for editing events seeded to communities.

EventSeedsQuery.summary: For container owners. API method for accessing events seeded to communities.

Events.summary: Deprecated API method for accessing meetup events. Please see /2/events and /2/open_events for replacements.

FindGroups.summary: Text, location, category and friend-based group searches

Groups.summary: API method for accessing meetup groups

Long-PollingCheckinsStream.summary:
This long-polling 
stream can be easily consumed using JavaScript in any modern browser. Checkin
notifications are received when they happen, or as soon as your script finishes handling its
last notification.

Long-PollingEventCommentsStream.summary:
This long-polling
stream can be easily consumed using JavaScript in any modern browser. Event Comment
notifications are received when they happen, or as soon as your script finishes handling its
last notification.

Long-PollingPhotoStream.summary:
This long-polling 
stream can be easily consumed using JavaScript in any modern browser. Photo upload
notifications are received when they happen, or as soon as your script finishes handling its
last notification.

Long-PollingRSVPStream.summary:
This long-polling 
stream can be easily consumed using JavaScript in any modern browser. RSVP
notifications are received when they happen, or as soon as your script finishes handling its
last notification.

MemberPhotoUpload.summary: Uploads a photo to be assocated with a Member

Members.summary: API method for accessing members of Meetup Groups

MembershipApproval.summary: Approves one or more requests for group membership

MessageCreate.summary: This method allows messaging-authorized requests to send messages between members

OpenEvents.summary: Searches for recent and upcoming public events hosted by Meetup groups. Its search window  is the past one month through the next three months, and is subject to change. Open Events is optimized to search for current events by location, category, topic, or text, and only lists Meetups that have 3 or more RSVPS. The number or results returned with each request is not guaranteed to be the same as the page size due to secondary filtering. If you're looking for a particular event or events within a particular group, use the standard Events method.

OpenEventsStream.summary:
Live HTTP stream of events within public Meetup groups. This method uses chunked
transfer encoding
to maintain a persistent connection with the client. This connection will only be
terminated for server maintenance or a connection error.

OpenVenues.summary: Searches for public venues within a given geo space. To search for specific venues that your group has used, use the Venues method

PhotoAlbum2.summary: This method creates photo albums within a Meetup group

PhotoAlbums.summary: This method returns photo albums associated with Meetup groups. To create albums, see the corresponding write method.

PhotoCommentsv2.summary: This method returns comments on meetup photos. To post messages, see the corresponding write method

PhotoCommentv2.summary: This method posts comments that appear below photos

Photos.summary: API method for accessing meetup photos

ProfileCreate(GroupJoin).summary: This method allows an authenticated member to join a group by creating a profile

Profiles.summary: This method returns member profiles associated with a particular group. Meetup members have separate profiles for each group they join.

RSVPsv2.summary: Query for Event RSVPs by event

Ratingsv2.summary: API method for accessing Meetup comments

RecommendedGroups.summary: Returns groups Meetup finds relevant to you

Rsvps.summary: API method for accessing meetup rsvps

Topics.summary: API method for accessing meetup topics

Venues.summary: Search for Meetup venues by one of your groups, events, or venue identifiers. For a full text search on public venues use OpenVenues.
